@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction:@{ub}

This program checks a file that holds the phone number of
the user that are calling and prints it in the BBS or before logon. 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}Installation:@{ub}

Copy files in archive to PFiles somewere and put this
at the END of line 29 in your BBStext:

#0PFiles:ANICheck/ANICheck.Rexx} 

If you do that the text will come up BEFORE user has logged in!
And you can offcorse use it wherever you want...

You can also put a command in BBSText under menu
2; Available everywhere like this:
ANI             `0- |#0PFiles:ANICheck/ANICheck.Rexx}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{b}Requirements:@{ub}

